courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students would be able to:
- Acquire an appreciation of how advanced technologies are impacting the business world everyday;
- Understand the cycle of problem discovery, motivating the design of innovation solutions;
- Gain practical experience in the design thinking process to nurture innovations;
- Acquire skills in project planning, group communication, discussion facilitation, team work and logical thinking skills through active class participation, article writing, collaborative problem solving and project presentation.

Upon completion of this course, students would be able to:

- Acquire sound understanding of the latest technologies that are impacting the business world every day;
- Understand the challenges faced by the business world in coping with changing business environments, higher customer sophistication and technological innovation;
- Gain practical experience in planning and delivering a group project on latest technologies;
- Acquire and practice planning, communication, facilitation, team work and logical thinking skills through active class participation, individual research paper and hands-on work on the final group project and presentation.

At the completion of the course, the students should have the ability to:
1. understand various important data analytics models and methods;
2. apply them to financial data to extract useful information for financial decision making;
3. implement the models and methods using Python or R.

Upon completion of this course, students would be able to:

* Acquire a solid understanding of the principles and concepts underlying GenAI technologies that are profoundly impacting the industry and society;
* Develop a strong foundation in GenAI, with practical skills for implementing and applying generative models to various domains;
* Develop an awareness of the ethical and social implications associated with GenAI. Students will be able to critically analyze issues such as bias, fairness, privacy, and the responsible deployment of generative models;
* Gain practical experience in planning and delivering a group project based on latest technologies.

Researchers and practitioners are invited to give seminars to share their experience with students on:

- The contemporary issues relevant to the discipline of operations research and information technology and their applications in engineering and managerial decision making, especially in financial services, logistics and supply chain management, business information systems, and service engineering and management;
- The approaches to identify, formulate, and solve engineering problems;
- The methods to design and conduct experiments, as well as to analyze and interpret data within realistic constraints, such as economic, environmental, social, political, ethical, health and safety, manufacturability and sustainability;
- The ways to use the techniques, skills, and modern engineering tools necessary for engineering practice along with an understanding of their processes and limitations;
- The impact of engineering solutions in a global and societal context, especially the importance of health, safety and environmental considerations;
- Presenting and delivering the research outputs effectively.

By completion of the course, students should have acquired more knowledge in developing and carrying out their own research.

